sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K235027
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: [K235024][K235000] (NAND gate control test, arabinose positive control)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This BioBrick is a control for the NAND gate (K235025). This system constitutively produces the ribolocked mRNA for the λcI repressor protein. It can therefore be used as a positive control for the arabinose segment of the system; only the presence or absence of IPTG should change the level of mCherry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kyliah Clarkson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Constructed using three-antibiotic assembly. On plasmid pSB1A3.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K235024
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This Biobrick will produce mCherry fluorescent protein (J06504) under the control of the λcI promoter. It will also constitutively produce mRNA for the λcI repressor protein (C0051). The protein will only be translated when a ribokey (i.e., J23066) is also present in the cell.
This system is sensitive to the cellular production of λcI repressor protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kyliah Clarkson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Constructed using three-antibiotic assembly. On plasmid pSB1C3.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K235021
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This BioBrick constitutively produced mRNA for the λcI repressor protein. It will not be translated unless a ribokey (i.e., J23066) is also present in the cell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kyliah Clarkson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Constructed using three-antibiotic assembly. On plasmid pSB1A3.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kyliah Clarkson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Constructed using three-antibiotic assembly. On plasmid pSB1C3.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K235018
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This BioBrick constitutively generates the mCherry fluorescent protein (J06504) unless the λcI repressor protein (i.e., C0051) is present in the cell.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kyliah Clarkson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Constructed using three-antibiotic assembly. On plasmid pSB1A3.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K235000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part generates a ribokey (J23066) under the control of the lactose promoter. The key will not be produced except in LacI-deficient strains, or when cultured with lactose or inducers such as IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kyliah Clarkson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Constructed using the three-antibiotic assembly method, is on plasmid pSB1C3

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cI repressor from E. coli phage lambda (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the cI repressor based on cI repressor from bacteriophage lambda modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein. cI repressor binds to the cI regulator (BBa_R0051).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999).

References (unparsed) here:

Octamerization of CI repressor is needed for effective repression of PRM and efficient switching from lysogeny. Ian B. Dodd,1 Alison J. Perkins, Daniel Tsemitsidis, and J. Barry Egan , Genes and Development (Vol 15, No. 22) 3013-3022: 2001

References (unparsed) here:

A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000

BBa_C0051 cI repressor is based on the cI repressor from the Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LAA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mCherry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: mRFP (DsRed) derived, altered to be a biobrick by removing a PstI site and adding in the ends.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ytwang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: mCherry from Roger Y. Tsien's lab, altered to be BioBrick compatible
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Made a point mutation to eliminate a PstI site in the middle and then added BioBrick ends using PCR.

Sequenced using primers that bind to the pSB1A2 plasmid on either side of the brick.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS based on Elowitz repressilator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The cI regulated promoter is based on the pR promtoer from bacteriohage lambda. The promoter has two two DNA binding sites for lambda cI repressor BBa_C0051. cI binding results in repression of transcription. The specific sequence used here is based on the cI repressible promoter used in the Elowitz repressilator (and references therein).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
In order to address concerns about the promoter transcribing in the reverse direction, we have removed the -35 and -10 signals responsible for the promoter activity in the reverse direction. (More details needed here! DE, 2/24/03)

Incompatible with host expressing cI repressor.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J23008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part has the same homology region to J01122 as J23007 except that unlike J23007, J23008 does not contain the hairpin that was derived from J01129. J23008 anneals linearly to the stem of the hairpin in J01122 with perfect base pairing and destroys the hairpin in the process and reveals the RBS on J01122. When J01122 is transcribed the RNA secondary structure is such that the RBS hairpins with sequence upstream preventing the ribosome from binding and translation from occuring thereby locking up RFP further down stream. When J23008 is introduced into the cell in trans, we suspect that it will unlock the RBS for RFP as described above allowing translation to occur.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kaitlin Davis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No design considerations

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J23009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Variant of key3 (see part J01129 (key3), J23007(key3b), J23008(key3c)). Part is in pJ23006, so there is a Ptet upstream of the XbaI site to drive expression. Nevertheless, J23009 is still a basic part allowing both prefix and suffix insertions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Overlap extension
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: N/A

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
